-- Saudi Arabia to Pursue ‘Ambitious’ Nuclear Program, SPA Reports
-- B y   G l e n   C a r e y
-- 2012-03-27T13:35:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-27/saudi-arabia-to-pursue-ambitious-nuclear-program-spa-reports.html
Saudi Arabia , the world’s largest
oil exporter, will adopt an “ambitious” program for the
peaceful use of nuclear energy, the official Saudi Press Agency
reported, citing Hashim Abdullah Yamani, the president of King
Abdullah City for Atomic and  Renewable Energy .  This is “in line with its strategic objectives to
diversify its energy sources,” the Riyadh-based news service
cited Yamani as saying at the Nuclear Security Summit in  Seoul .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Glen Carey in Riyadh at 
 gcarey8@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Andrew J. Barden at 
 barden@bloomberg.net  